<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="248" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,511,896]" pageId="1" pageNumber="248">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,511,536]" pageId="1" pageNumber="248">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Members of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[538,642,512,535]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acrotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[538,642,512,535]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="248">Acrotona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other athetine genera by combination of the following characters: body fusiform, more or less convex dorso-ventrally; infraorbital carina complete; pronotum transverse, widest behind middle, pubescence directed posteriorly in midline in most; hypomera invisible in lateral aspect; mesoventral process beyond middle of mesocoxal cavities; metatarsomere 1–4 subequal in length; abdomen narrow apically, with conspicuous macrosetae; segmental margins of abdomen minutely crenulate; abdominal tergites III–V impressed in basal region, VII longer than VI; bursa of spermatheca more or less spherical and extended to elongate neck, duct regularly coiled posteriorly and often with swelled apex (
<bibRefCitation author="Fenyes, A." box="[1211,1366,728,752]" pageId="1" pageNumber="248" pagination="114 - 414" refId="ref11402" refString="Fenyes, A. (1920) Coleoptera Fam. Staphylinidae subfam. Aleocharinae. In: Wytsman, P. (Eds.), Genera Insectorum. Fascicle 173 b. Louis Desmet-Verteneuil, Bruxelles, pp. 114 - 414." type="book chapter" year="1920">Fenyes, 1920</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Yosii, R. &amp; Sawada, K." pageId="1" pageNumber="248" pagination="11 - 140" refId="ref12754" refString="Yosii, R. &amp; Sawada, K. (1976) Studies on the genus Atheta Thomson and its allies (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). II: Diagnostic characters of genera and subgenera with description of representative species. Contributions from the Biological Laboratory, Kyoto University, 25 (1), 11 - 140." type="journal article" year="1976">Yosii &amp; Sawada, 1976</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Seevers, C. H." box="[351,512,764,788]" pageId="1" pageNumber="248" pagination="1 - 289" refId="ref12354" refString="Seevers, C. H. (1978) A generic and tribal revision of the North American Aleocharinae (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae) Fieldiana: Zoology, 71, 1 - 289." type="journal article" year="1978">Seevers, 1978</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lohse, G. A. &amp; Klimaszewski, J. &amp; Smetana, A." box="[523,728,764,789]" pageId="1" pageNumber="248" pagination="121 - 202" refId="ref11595" refString="Lohse, G. A., Klimaszewski, J. &amp; Smetana, A. (1990) Revision of arctic Aleocharinae of North America (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). The Coleopterists Bulletin, 44, 121 - 202." type="journal article" year="1990">
Lohse 
<emphasis box="[599,648,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="248">et al</emphasis>
., 1990
</bibRefCitation>
; Klimaszewski1 
<emphasis box="[919,968,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="248">et al</emphasis>
., 2015).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,491,799,824]" pageId="1" pageNumber="248" type="distribution">
